title: Strictly Come Dancing Grand Final
description:
Part One Jay McGuinness, Kellie Bright, Georgia May Foote, Katie Derham and their professional partners gather one last 

time for the 2015 Grand Final. Tensions are high as, after 13 weeks of performances, the celebrities face yet more turns 

on the dance floor. Tonight, the contestants will be hoping the judges will be kind with more than just their scores, as 

Len Goodman, Darcey Bussell, Craig Revel Horwood and Bruno Tonioli will also be deciding which of the stars' previous 

routines will be revisited in the first of tonight's dances. For their second performance, the duos must dazzle both the 

panel and the audience at home with their `show dance'. Once all eight routines are complete, the phone lines will open, 

giving viewers a chance to decide which of the competitors will be progressing through to the final three
Read more at http://www.tvguide.co.uk/detail/2264448/113726156/strictly-come-dancing-grand-final#7VBstggFrBThwHBq.99


Part Two The results of the viewers' votes have been counted, and the fourth-placed couple exits the competition, leaving 

the final three to battle it out with one last trio of performances. For this final round, the stars are given a chance 

to revisit their favourite routine from throughout the series, and once all three are complete, lines open to allow the 

viewing public to decide this year's winner. As ever, the Grand Final is accompanied by an appearance by a special 

musical guest, and as the champion is crowned, all of this year's contestants are invited back to the dance-floor for a 

star-studded group number. Last in the series

Category: General Show/Game Show

Executive Producer: Louise Rainbow
Series Director: Nikki Parsons

Cast
Host Tess Daly  (IMDB)
Host Claudia Winkleman  (IMDB)
Judge Craig Revel Horwood  (IMDB)
Judge Bruno Tonioli  (IMDB)

BBC1 London
